Welcome and thanks for choosing the ECALpro tools!


1) Run on a Gun:
./RunOnBatch.py All the parameters you need to run on MC, using ./Method_data.py create all the cfg file you need and launch the Analyzer.
you can launch the deamon to run for you:
bsub -q 1nw -o RunOnBatch_Daemon.log "bash /afs/cern.ch/work/l/lpernie/ECALpro/ETA_TRY/CMSSW_4_2_4/src/Analysis/Modules/test/RunOnBatch_Daemon.sh"

------

2) Run on Data:

./parameters_data.py -> All the parameters you need to run on a dataset
./RunOnBatch_data.py -> The file that using ./Method_data.py create all the cfg file you need and launch the Analyzer.
you can launch the deamon to run for you:
bsub -q 1nw -o RunOnBatch_Daemon.log "bash /afs/cern.ch/work/l/lpernie/ECALpro/ETA_TRY/CMSSW_4_2_4/src/Analysis/Modules/test/RunOnBatch_Daemon.sh"

------

For more questions: luca.pernie@cern.ch

Best,
LP
